about: The Event will be arcade styled i.e., initially the event will be Player vs Player, player who wins will continue to play unless he/she gets defeated.

Several adventurous phases where the teams will be allowed to roam the entire campus and look for treasure items (to find hidden objects/places). Each clue will have a particular story plot question which needs to be answered to solve a particular level.

Obstacle drone racing is a test of pilot's ability to beat other competitors by racing around specially built courses by crossing various obstacles to reach the finish line in the fastest time. Pilots may practice at the designated practice fields before the event. Limited practice runs would be provided to the participants. The participants are supposed to cross various hurdles such as Hula Hoops, Balloons etc. while flying the drone in order for the drones to reach the finish line.

Coding with Arduino would put your critical thinking and technical skills in the same boat. In this event a participant has to design an Arduino circuit according to a given problem statement. An on-spot designing contest, an open-ended problem statement will be provided for the registered groups for which they are expected to design an Arduino circuit (which meets the requirements). Participants are expected to Implement the Arduino circuit design.

It will be an exciting event as the name suggests CODE2WIN to challenge the technical skills within a particular given time. Participants will have the option of choosing either of the three difficulty levels (Easy, Medium, Hard) and within a specific time frame they have to solve either one question for winning a single prize or solve 2 Questions for winning double prizes.Questions will test the coding ability of participants at various difficulty levels. There will be exciting rewards such as amazon vouchers, goodies etc.
